	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />All good points. I guess personally if I were making a game I'd be more inclined to make something more like Castlevania or Mega Man. Cause as you know there is a severe lack of platformers on the NES. =) That and I'd rather have a fixed bank than deal with 32K switching. Not that it'd be too difficult to handle, the easiest thing would be duplicating certain things in the upper part of every bank but then that wastes memory. Memory might not be that big of a deal though. <br /><br />But obviously with discrete mappers you have lots of choices and lots of things you can expand on pretty easily. You don't have to have a MMC5 or MMC3 to make a great game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
